Me too :-)
Kernel version 2.2.9
PCMCIA version 3.0.8
Using DHCP on the interface.
    - poorer new version that camps on the interface preventing card eject
Probable .config attached (it's dated 27th may!)
The machine is a portable, the interface a 3com combined serial/ether
using the 3c589_cs module on an i82365 interface. The incidence is rare
for me and only happened after an APM suspend to disk (when the ether
card is inserted of course).
